"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to urge, implore"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/naː.ʃa.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39804","headword_ar":"نَاشِدٌ","root":"n$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$ada","text_ar":"نَشَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the following verse of Aboo-Du-ád,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"watuSiyxu A^aHoyaAnFA kamaA A@so\n                      \n                     \n                        tamaEa AlmuDil~u liSawoti naA$ido"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And she listens sometimes like as he who has lost a beast gives ear to the voice of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nA$d","text_ar":"ناشد"},{"kind":"text","text":"], signifies a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man making known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"giving information of, a stray-best:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one seeking for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after, a stray-beast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he who has lost a beast desires to find one who, like himself, has lost one, that he may be consoled thereby. (S, M, L.) See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swx","text_ar":"صوخ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naA$iduwna","text_ar":"نَاشِدُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Men who seek after straycamels, and take them, and confine them from their owners."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}